{{Quote|I suggest you leave this shuttle&hellip;unless you wish to be put into service in the ''Sulphur Pits'' of ''Vulcar''!|[[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], to [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]]|<ref name="The Destroyer" />}}
The '''Sulphur Pits of Vulcar''' were [[Sulfur/Legends|sulfur]] pits<ref name="The Destroyer" /> located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Vulcar]] that were [[Mining/Legends|mined]] for [[oridium]] deposits. The world's acrid [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]] made employing [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] workers barely cost-effective. As a result, Vulcar was primarily worked by [[Droid/Legends|droids]] of all types, including [[KM1 mining droid|crab droids]], reprogrammed to serve as [[Miner/Legends|miners]] until they froze up and rusted into scrap.<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[15 BBY/Legends|15 BBY]], an [[Intergalactic Droid Agency]] [[Intergalactic Droid Agency shuttle|shuttle]] traveled to the Sulphur Pits of Vulcar<ref name="The Droids Re-Animated">{{SW|url=news/the-droids-re-animated-part-1|series=The Droids Re-Animated|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> after delivering the droids [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] to the planet [[Dodz]].<ref name="The Destroyer" />

==Behind the scenes==
Vulcar was first mentioned in [[Droids (1986) 1|''Droids'' (1986) 1]], the first issue of the [[Star Wars: Droids (1986)|''Star Wars: Droids'']] comic series published by [[Star Comics]], an imprint of [[Marvel Comics]],<ref name="The Destroyer" /> which was first published on [[April 1]], [[1986]].<ref name="The Destroyer publication date">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/54151/star_wars_droids_1986_1|text=Star Wars: Droids (1986) #1}}</ref>

